FORMER Rhythmic Elements percussionist Teekay Kotu has died. The news of his death was posted on social media by people who flooded his Facebook wall and said they couldn’t believe he was really gone. His cause of death hasn’t been announced yet. Teekay was known for being a percussionist for duo Rhythmic Elements which made hits like Hello Mr. and 2 By 2. One half of Rhythmic Elements, Mpho “McKenzie” Matome, took to social media to thank him for the time they spent together. ALSO READ : TNS GIVES HIS DESIGNER CLOTHES TO THE HOMELESS! “Thank you for the time, the energy and the laughter. The memories of you. Till we meet again. RIP,” he wrote. Facebook user Peter Petmuso Baloyi said Teekay was a legend. “You had a larger than life personality bro. It seemed like you would live forever, your passing is a sad one, you had more to give. You had that ability to make people laugh without trying, laughter was the order of the day as long as you were around bro. I’m fortunate to have shared music moments with you bro. You always encouraged n saw the best in me. I will remember that bro. You were a LEGEND, RIP!” he wrote. Singer Kelly Khumalo also posted about Teekay and his memorial service details. They had recently released a song titled Passop together late last year. His memorial service will be held at Cafe Sphettino in Ga-Rankuwa, Tshwane on Thursday, 27 January.   A post shared by The Voice Of Africa (@kellykhumaloza)  